Currently, only a few shrines still worship Gozu Tennō directly. Most shrines now enshrine {{ill|Susanoo|ja|スサノオ}}, who was syncretized with Gozu Tennō under {{ill|Shinbutsu-shūgō|ja|神仏習合}}. During the {{ill|Shinbutsu bunri|ja|神仏分離}} (separation of Shinto and Buddhism) in the {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治}}, some shrines reverted to deities listed in ancient records other than Susanoo.

Since the Meiji period, many shrines have been merged with others or renamed to align with the Tsushima Gozu Tennōsha, such as renaming to {{ill|Tsushima Shrine|ja|津島神社}}. As a result of Shinbutsu bunri and shrine mergers, some shrines now enshrine deities other than Gozu Tennō or interpret Gozu Tennō as a deity distinct from Susanoo. In some regions, the influence of these shrines can still be seen in place names incorporating "Tenno."

== List ==
* {{ill|Tenno Shrine (Shichinohe)|ja|天王神社 (七戸町)}} - Aomori Prefecture, Kamikita District, Shichinohe, {{ill|Shichinohe|ja|七戸 (七戸町)}}
* {{ill|Susanoo Shrine (Shibata)|ja|須佐之男神社 (新発田市)}} (Tenno Shrine) - Niigata Prefecture, Shibata, {{ill|Tenno (Shibata)|ja|天王 (新発田市)}}<ref>[http://www.niigata-kankou.or.jp/sys/data?page-id=10163], [http://www.niigata-u.com/files/ngt2009g/091010b1.html], [http://shibata-info.jp/archives/eventcal/%E5%A4%A9%E7%8E%8B%E3%81%BE%E3%81%A4%E3%82%8A]</ref>
* {{ill|Tenno Shrine (Kameoka)|ja|天王神社 (亀岡市)}} - Kyoto Prefecture, Kameoka, {{ill|Miyamae Town|ja|宮前町 (亀岡市)}}, Kamisaki, Tenno Shita<ref>[http://agua.jpn.org/film/f99.html], [http://901-1000.wakkan.jp/927.html]</ref>
* {{ill|Tenno Shrine Hachiman Shrine|ja|天王社八幡宮}}
* {{ill|Tenno Shrine (Kizugawa)|ja|天王神社 (木津川市)}} - Kyoto Prefecture, Kizugawa, {{ill|Kizu Shimizu|ja|木津清水}}
* {{ill|Tenno Shrine (Komatsushima)|ja|天王社 (小松島市)}} - Tokushima Prefecture, Komatsushima, {{ill|Tano Town (Komatsushima)|ja|田野町 (小松島市)}}
* {{ill|Gozu Tenno Shrine|ja|牛頭天王神社}}
* {{ill|Tenno Hachiman Shrine|ja|天王八幡神社}}
* {{ill|Kenoda Suga Shrine|ja|健田須賀神社}}

